<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1157">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/50.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Spanish Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 218.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-06">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to
                                acknowledge the receipt of your note<note n="2" xml:id="d1157fn2">Not printed.</note> of December 4, in which you inform the
                                Department that you have received a telegram from the Minister of
                                Spain at Mexico <pb facs="1006" n="902" xml:id="pg_902"/> City in
                                which he asks you to request this Department to send urgent
                                instructions to the American Consul at Chihuahua, Mexico, to use his
                                good offices to the end that the foreign and Mexican residents there
                                be respected by the revolutionists.</p>
                            <p>In reply I beg to inform you that, in accordance with your request
                                that your colleague’s wishes be complied with, the Department has
                                sent to the American Consuls at Chihuahua and Juárez appropriate
                                instructions in the premises.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>.</signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>